A.1 — Contact-update photo clobber (corpus-wide loss disclosed 2026-04-26)
==========================================================================
Every contact updated through nc_contacts_update_contact lost its PHOTO
blob silently. Recovery merge of 162 contacts / 142 photos from a
2026-03-13 backup is at Downloads/2026-04-26_merged-from-2026-03-13.vcf.
Mankind Grooming was the canonical victim — photo + cell number + barber
name (Kosta) all silently absent post-update.

Root cause (verified by source inspection 2026-04-27): the legacy
_merge_vcard_properties used naive split("\n") + strip() which broke
RFC 5545 §3.1 line folding. PHOTO base64 continuation lines lost their
leading-whitespace fold marker, were misclassified as standalone
properties, and re-joined with \n only — corrupting the on-wire vCard
the server then dropped the PHOTO from. Plan's diagnosis (JSON↔vCard
round-trip) was approximate; the actual bug is in the text-merge path.

Fix: new nextcloud_mcp_server/client/vcard_parser.py implements a
line-oriented byte-preserving parser. Untouched lines emit verbatim from
their original_bytes; modified lines regenerate per RFC 6350 §3.2 +
RFC 5545 §3.1. PHOTO blobs treated as opaque base64.

A.3 — Schema gaps for non-Latin / non-standard vCards
======================================================
Address-book corpus surveys during recovery showed: some contacts have
no UID (older ez-vcard 0.12.1 exports), some have no FN (ORG-only
contacts), and emoji-bearing FN fields need NFC normalisation.

Fix: models/contacts.py — Contact.uid / Contact.fn now Optional. New
Contact.display_name resolves FN → ORG → "given family" → opaque
placeholder. synthesize_uid() derives stable SHA1-based UIDs from raw
content. NFC normalisation on string fields used for matching.

Unified 8-op nc_contacts_* tool surface (Gary 2026-04-27 directive)
====================================================================
1. nc_contacts_list_addressbooks         (existing; no change)
2. nc_contacts_list_contacts             (gains include_vcard / include_etag)
3. nc_contacts_get_contact               NEW (vcard_text + etag + json)
4. nc_contacts_create_contact            (accepts vcard_text or JSON)
5. nc_contacts_patch_contact             NEW (surgical edit, If-Match)
6. nc_contacts_put_contact               NEW (full vCard replace, If-Match)
7. nc_contacts_delete_contact            (gains If-Match)
8. nc_contacts_create_addressbook + nc_contacts_delete_addressbook
                                         (existing; admin pair counted as one)

nc_contacts_update_contact is DEPRECATED — surgical-edit semantics differ
enough from the legacy JSON-roundtripping behaviour that keeping the same
name with reworked behaviour would surprise existing callers. The shim
remains, translating JSON-shape calls to patch_contact under the byte-
preserving substrate, with a logger.warning on each invocation. One
minor version, then removed.

ETag / If-Match discipline
==========================
Every write surfaces 412 to the caller as EtagConflictError; no silent
retries unless the caller opts in via retry_on_conflict=True on
patch_contact. Optional verify=True triggers post-write GET to detect
structural-loss bugs in the substrate itself (returns 409 -> raise
VerifyMismatchError when the change is missing post-PUT).

Verification
============
tests/client/contacts/test_byte_preserving.py — full T1-T10 corpus
(plan §A.1) + A.3 schema-gap tests + bonus tests (LF endings, X-prop
removal). All 16 tests pass against the new parser. The Mankind
Grooming end-to-end test (T1b) is the canonical guard: a targeted
NOTE edit preserves the PHOTO blob, both X-properties, all multi-TYPE
TEL lines, and the REV.

